		<p class="postmetadata">  by Jim</p>
		<p>2011 Capital Gains Tax Rates One of the changes Bush implemented was an calibrating to the tax brackets themselves. Many of those cuts are set to come to an end this year, the two big items being takings tax rates and capital gains rates.  When people talk about the Bush-era tax cuts, they’re as a rule referring to the Financial Flowering and Tax Substitute Propitiation Act of 2001 (EGTRRA) signed by President Bush in June of 2001. The Budgetary Cultivation and Tax Alleviation Pacification Act of 2001 introduced a 10% tax bracket and the brackets themselves were lowered. If we take the pre-cut brackets along with the pre-cut capital gains rates, we have the following:. President Obama has publicly said that he will let the Bush-era capital gains tax cuts run out on register this year, so it’s well-connected to have knowledge of how they will assume your investments....</p>
